TopicTitle: Fresh KSP 1.1 Install (Just bought it) Constantly Crashing

Articles.Content:
I've been able to complete a couple of the training tutorials but the game crashes at random times.

Here is my setup

i3-4170 - 8GB Kingston Hyper Fury - XFX AMD R9 380 4GB (no over clocking) - 120 GB SSD - 1TB HDD - Windows 10 Pro 64Bit

I'm not having any heat related issues and the system doesn't seem to be suffering from memory leaks that I can tell but I'll keep trying and monitoring to make sure.  The crashes are unpredictable and happen at random times.  I'm really excited to play this game and have waited forever to finally purchase it (had to save up).  I hope there is a fix coming down the pipe and feel free to ask me for more info if I'm able to provide it.

Unfortunately I am unable to find any information on where KSP puts the Crash Logs (there are none in the main directory) so I don't know how I could retrieve them.
The crash logs are found in seperate folder insite the main folder.

This sticky thread in this sub-forum describes exactly where the log files can be found:

In addition, some crashes will cause the game to create a folder in your KSP folder named with the date and time that you ran KSP (e.g. "2016-04-08_163858" for 16:38:58 on 8th April 2016) and put various useful files in it.  If you get one of these folders then best to simply zip that up and upload the whole thing rather than just the output_log.txt.

I am also having this problem with a newly bought KSP

Tried both the 32 and 64-bit for Steam on Windows 10. Eventually crashes when building any ship. Variable amount of time before it does though. (It doesn't immediately crash, I can get some play time in)

I "verified the integrity of game cache..." with Steam, and it said 3 files were missing and added them; though that doesn't seem to have helped any.
